description: Never use competitor brand names in user-facing product copy
alwaysApply: true
---

# Product voice — Cadence only

In any **user-facing** UI, marketing, App Store / Play Store copy, onboarding, or settings:

- Do **not** name competitors or third-party note apps (e.g. Notion, Obsidian, Heptabase, Roam, Logseq, Evernote, OneNote, Word, PowerPoint) as positioning (“inspired by”, “Notion-like”, “Obsidian-style”).
- Describe features in Cadence’s own words (知識庫、連結圖、日誌、看板、白板、簡報模式).
- File format labels are OK when they are formats (`.md`, `.docx`, `PDF`), not brand slogans.
- Internal docs / `ROADMAP.md` may mention reference products for engineering planning only — never surface that language in the shipped app.
